{"TopicId":179185,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal Space Program needs borderless windowed option","CreatedByName":"Autolyzed Yeast Extract","CreatedById":168053,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T18:16:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Autolyzed Yeast Extract","CreatedById":168053,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T18:16:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease developers please\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-22T18:34:14Z\u0022 title=\u002210/22/2018 06:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Autolyzed Yeast Extract\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T18:55:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you explain why this would be beneficial?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T19:01:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s already there, a command line option.\u00A0 I think it is -popupwindow\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223473292\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540234515\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you explain why this would be beneficial?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have multiple screens, it prevents the game from being back grounded if you click outside the window.\u00A0 I use this all the time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Autolyzed Yeast Extract","CreatedById":168053,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T19:33:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223473294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540234917\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s already there, a command line option.\u00A0 I think it is -popupwindow\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have multiple screens, it prevents the game from being back grounded if you click outside the window.\u00A0 I use this all the time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni will try now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Autolyzed Yeast Extract","CreatedById":168053,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T20:22:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit works but i\u0027d prefer if it was a in game setting\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-22T20:23:25Z\u0022 title=\u002210/22/2018 08:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Autolyzed Yeast Extract\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T20:38:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nComplain to Unity.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Autolyzed Yeast Extract","CreatedById":168053,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T20:40:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\npoint taken\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T21:48:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223473364\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540240706\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nComplain to Unity.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI swear you could use this option from the launcher at one point in time.\u00A0 It was oddly still not an option within the game itself.\u00A0 That being said, did Unity remove this?\u00A0 ...or did KSP\u0027s launcher work around it some how?\u00A0 I still have old versions of KSP to confirm whether I\u0027m crazy or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T22:03:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223473405\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540244898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105132\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klgraham1013\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, klgraham1013 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI swear you could use this option from the launcher at one point in time.\u00A0 It was oddly still not an option within the game itself.\u00A0 That being said, did Unity remove this?\u00A0 ...or did KSP\u0027s launcher work around it some how?\u00A0 I still have old versions of KSP to confirm whether I\u0027m crazy or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Correct. Using the launcher you were able to tell it because the launcher was launching KSP as a separate program, and therefore was able to specify the option to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JedTech","CreatedById":104003,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T22:30:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is all possible. Try this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nCreate a shortcut with startup parameter\u00A0-popupwindow.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nLaunch the game using your customized shortcut.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nGo to settings and change resolution to your screen size.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUncheck Full Screen. --very important.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nThis allows me to mouse over to other monitors while KSP remains in focus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nSee this for more details on startup parameters.:\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Startup_parameters\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Startup_parameters\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-22T22:35:58Z\u0022 title=\u002210/22/2018 10:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by JedTech\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Autolyzed Yeast Extract","CreatedById":168053,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T22:35:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027ve got it to work already\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}